ved alongside the largest chrysotile asbestos mine in the world. Dependent on this deadly industry for their community’s survival, they developed a unique, place-based understanding of their local environment; the risks they faced living next to the giant opencast mine; and their place within the global resource trade. This book unearths the local-global tensions that defined Asbestos’s proud history and reveals the challenges similar resource communities have faced – and continue to face today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAsbestos industryxPolitical aspectszQuébec (Province)zAsbestos. 0aAsbestos industryzQuébec (Province)zAsbestos. 0aAsbestos industry--Quâebec (Province)--History. 0aAsbestos mines and miningxEnvironmental aspectszQuébec (Province)zAsbestos. 0aAsbestos mines and miningxHealth aspectszQuébec (Province)zAsbestos. 0aAsbestos mines and miningzQuébec (Province)zAsbestos. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Disease & Health Issues.2bisacsh1 aWynn, Graeme, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311127380808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2016z978311127630408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311141795040uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077482843740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774828437423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774828437/original  a978-3-11-127380-8  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-127630-4  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-141795-0  University of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles